@bolkedebruin @gsakkis this PR is causing test failures -- #2018 added code to `tests/jobs.py` that depends on the `from airflow import models` line that this PR removes. Now all tests are failing with a "NameError: global name 'models' is not defined" message.

It looks like the local branch unit tests ran fine when the PR was submitted, but then #2018 was merged a few days ago. Not sure why travis didn't run here though it probably wouldn't have caught the issue unless the PR was rebased on to master prior to merge. 

I will submit a PR to fix it asap.
